      "document_id": "MD13374",
      "title": "भारतीय įरज़वर् बैंक RESERVE BANK OF INDIA",
      "text": "भारतीय įरज़वर् बैंक RESERVE BANK OF INDIA\nwww.rbi.org.in\nRBI/DPSS/2026-27/396\nRBI/CO.DPSS.POLC.No.S56/02.14.003/2026-27\n\n April 21, 2026\nIndex Introduction Short Title and Commencement Applicability Definitions Registration and revocation of E-mandate Processing of First Transaction and Subsequent Recurring Transactions Pre-Transaction Notification Post-Transaction Notification Transaction Limits and Velocity Check Dispute Resolution and Grievance Redressal Other Provisions Repeal\nDigital Payments - E-mandate Framework, 2026\nIn exercise of the powers conferred by Sections 10(2) read with Section 18 of the\nPayment and Settlement Systems (PSS) Act, 2007, the Reserve Bank of India (RBI),\nbeing satisfied that it is necessary and expedient in the public interest so to do,\nhereby consolidates all circulars pertaining to e-mandates and issues the Directions\nhereinafter specified.",
